WEBVTT

00:00.187 --> 00:01.136
There are two kinds of folks

00:01.193 --> 00:02.793
who sit around thinking
about how to kill people:

00:03.127 --> 00:04.853
Psychopaths
and mystery writers.

00:05.091 --> 00:06.113
I'm the kind that pays better.

00:06.514 --> 00:07.114
Who am I?

00:07.203 --> 00:08.342
I'm Rick Castle.

00:08.343 --> 00:08.743
Castle.

00:08.777 --> 00:09.437
Castle.

00:09.438 --> 00:11.138
I really am ruggedly handsome,
aren't I?

00:11.192 --> 00:13.382
Every writer needs inspiration.
And I found mine.

00:13.592 --> 00:14.411
Detective Kate Beckett.

00:14.658 --> 00:15.925
Beckett.
Aah!

00:16.198 --> 00:18.283
Beckett?
Could you get some backup, please?

00:18.634 --> 00:20.518
<i>And thanks to my friendship</i>
<i>with the Mayor,</i>

00:20.569 --> 00:22.203
<i>I get to be on her case.</i>
Oh!

00:22.237 --> 00:24.806
Do I look like a killer to you?
Yes, you kill my patience.

00:24.840 --> 00:26.474
<i>And together,</i>
<i>we catch killers.</i>

00:27.022 --> 00:29.924
I hate this case.
I know. Isn't it great?

00:30.446 --> 00:32.046
Ephraim Mankofsky,

00:32.081 --> 00:35.317
or simply Mank,
as he liked to be called,

00:35.351 --> 00:37.185
lived a fruitful life.

00:37.220 --> 00:40.755
A proud father
of ten wonderful children...

00:40.790 --> 00:45.660
Mank was so very,
very blessed.

00:47.830 --> 00:49.097
Ah!

00:51.567 --> 00:54.236
Oh!
Oh.

00:54.270 --> 00:56.037
Who's the shiksa?

00:56.462 --> 00:58.763
I'm thinking
bubblegum fantasy...

00:58.797 --> 01:01.947
Mm-Hmm
or maybe frosted iris.

01:02.047 --> 01:05.015
I'm thinking tickle-the-toe red.
It's my go-to color.

01:06.485 --> 01:07.985
Oh.

01:08.019 --> 01:09.487
You expecting someone?

01:09.488 --> 01:11.828
Gina got promotional freebies
at a new spa

01:11.928 --> 01:14.735
and asked us if we wanted to go
get manis, pedis, and massages.

01:15.065 --> 01:16.498
And <i>you're</i> going?

01:16.533 --> 01:18.134
When it comes to
your ex-wife, darling,

01:18.234 --> 01:20.969
perks outweigh
personal considerations.

01:21.003 --> 01:23.271
- Hello.
- Hello.

01:23.306 --> 01:25.040
You look great.
Well, thank you.

01:26.424 --> 01:28.793
Uh, am I invited?

01:28.805 --> 01:30.706
Uh, no.
It's a girls' day out.

01:30.740 --> 01:33.008
I want to spend time
with Martha and Alexis.

01:33.042 --> 01:34.476
Uh, but I love massages,

01:34.511 --> 01:36.912
and I don't want
the three of you conspiring.

01:36.946 --> 01:37.662
Don't worry, dad.

01:37.762 --> 01:39.462
We've got a lot of other stuff
to talk about.

01:39.562 --> 01:41.864
I want to hear all about
Alexis' new boyfriend

01:41.898 --> 01:43.365
from her point of view.

01:43.400 --> 01:45.953
Did you know
that they have a song?

01:46.053 --> 01:47.112
You have a song?

01:47.213 --> 01:48.947
Yeah. Taylor Swift's "Mine."

01:48.982 --> 01:50.312
It was playing the first time
Ash and I kissed-

01:50.512 --> 01:51.417
La, la, la, la.

01:51.518 --> 01:53.352
I don't want to hear that.

01:53.386 --> 01:55.588
That's why I wanted
those tickets so badly.

01:55.661 --> 01:57.561
Taylor's playing an exclusive
acoustic show on Tuesday,

01:57.596 --> 01:59.764
and I wanted to take Ash,
but it was sold out

01:59.831 --> 02:01.003
before we could get tickets.

02:01.203 --> 02:04.184
Well, have you checked on eBay
or your father's ticket broker?

02:04.452 --> 02:05.886
The only ones available

02:05.920 --> 02:07.821
would've cost Ash and I
six years of allowance...

02:07.855 --> 02:09.222
Ah, well.
Each.

02:09.257 --> 02:11.591
- Mm.
- Do you remember our song?

02:11.626 --> 02:14.261
AC/DC's "You Shook Me
All Night Long."

02:14.295 --> 02:16.414
La, la, la, la.
Don't want to hear it.
Ohh.

02:16.514 --> 02:18.414
You girls have a great day.

02:18.449 --> 02:20.550
Remember, it won't be
the same without me.
No.

02:22.553 --> 02:24.554
Mm.

02:25.723 --> 02:28.391
Mm. Looks like
you have plans anyway.

02:32.957 --> 02:35.061
Don't we usually get to
the victim before the funeral?

02:35.910 --> 02:37.242
What have we got?

02:37.342 --> 02:39.310
Mourners found a body
in the casket.

02:39.344 --> 02:41.245
And that's unusual how?

02:41.279 --> 02:42.980
Well,
the family was bidding

02:43.014 --> 02:44.748
a fond farewell
to Mr. Mank here,

02:44.783 --> 02:46.684
and discovered that he wasn't
going to the grave alone.

02:46.718 --> 02:49.286
Is it just me,
or is Mr. Mank smiling?

02:49.321 --> 02:52.056
Our stowaway
is Dr. Valerie Monroe,

02:52.090 --> 02:55.030
an attending internist
at County Hospital.

02:55.345 --> 02:57.480
A doctor? Any connection
to the deceased?

02:57.573 --> 02:58.879
Ryan's talking
to the family now

02:59.079 --> 02:59.700
Cause of death?

02:59.800 --> 03:02.001
Liver failure.
He drank like a fish.

03:02.036 --> 03:05.822
We may know what killed
Mr. Mank,

03:05.922 --> 03:08.405
but your dead doctor here
is more of a mystery.

03:08.824 --> 03:11.159
No bullet holes, stab wounds
or ligature marks.

03:11.193 --> 03:13.695
She has a perimortem bruise

03:13.729 --> 03:16.031
on the back of her neck here,

03:16.065 --> 03:17.999
but it wasn't severe enough
to have been fatal.

03:18.034 --> 03:19.935
Lividity indicates she died

03:19.969 --> 03:21.870
sometime between
7:00 and 9:00 last night.

03:21.904 --> 03:23.805
But until I can perform
an autopsy,

03:23.839 --> 03:25.086
cause of death is unknown.

03:25.286 --> 03:25.820
Well, what we do know

03:25.920 --> 03:28.060
is that somebody was trying
to get rid of her body.

03:28.153 --> 03:30.136
Along with her purse
and her phone.

03:30.336 --> 03:32.202
You know, it's kind of brilliant
when you think about it--

03:32.376 --> 03:35.177
disappearing a body
in an already occupied coffin.

03:35.212 --> 03:37.146
And because
Jewish tradition demands

03:37.180 --> 03:38.158
that you bury the body
right away,

03:38.258 --> 03:39.332
there's less time
to get caught.

03:39.432 --> 03:41.192
And if it wasn't for
the pallbearers' fumble,

03:41.261 --> 03:43.298
the good doctor would've
disappeared forever.

03:43.398 --> 03:44.532
All right. Talk to
the funeral director.

03:44.632 --> 03:47.753
See if anyone had access to this
coffin in the last 24 hours.

03:48.360 --> 03:50.268
I'm telling you,
I don't know her.

03:50.300 --> 03:51.334
I've never seen her before,

03:51.359 --> 03:54.131
and I have no idea how
her body got in that casket.

03:54.193 --> 03:55.548
This morning when I came in,

03:55.567 --> 03:57.589
I found one of
my back windows smashed.

03:57.689 --> 03:59.176
So you're saying somebody
broke in here

03:59.369 --> 04:00.893
and stashed a body
in one of your coffins?

04:00.974 --> 04:03.375
I called the police,
but since nothing was missing,

04:03.510 --> 04:05.911
you guys didn't bother
showinup. Maybe if you had,

04:05.979 --> 04:08.447
I wouldn't have Mrs. Manks
out for my blood.

04:10.316 --> 04:12.083
So according
to County Hospital,

04:12.117 --> 04:16.224
Dr. Monroe finished her shift
at 6:00 P.M. last night,

04:16.386 --> 04:20.122
which is about an hour or two
before she was murdered,

04:20.156 --> 04:22.224
so hopefully her colleagues
will be able to tell us

04:22.258 --> 04:24.493
where she was headed.

04:25.314 --> 04:26.981
Castle, stop playing
with her phone.

04:27.046 --> 04:28.613
I wasn't playing.

04:28.648 --> 04:30.549
I wasn't. The last
Web searches on her phone

04:30.583 --> 04:32.484
were after
6:00 P.M. yesterday.

04:32.518 --> 04:34.453
She was looking for a hotel
in Katonah, New York.

04:34.487 --> 04:35.798
I thought
it might be relevant.

04:39.093 --> 04:40.727
Oh.

04:40.761 --> 04:42.729
She also has
the new slot car app,

04:42.763 --> 04:46.533
so I'm thinking maybe she has
friends or family in Katonah.

04:46.567 --> 04:48.702
Or perhaps she was planning
a liaison with her lover.

04:48.736 --> 04:49.863
Her boyfriend found out,

04:49.963 --> 04:51.115
and killed her
in a jealous rage.

04:51.215 --> 04:52.398
Yeah, no visible marks
on her body

04:52.499 --> 04:54.834
other than a small bruise
on the back of her neck--

04:54.868 --> 04:56.397
that sounds like
a jealous rage to me.

04:56.497 --> 04:57.470
Castle.

04:58.569 --> 05:00.103
For you.
Oh, yes! Thank you.

05:00.145 --> 05:01.321
Are you
getting mail here now?

05:01.371 --> 05:04.072
Only when I don't want
my daughter to see it.

05:04.107 --> 05:06.167
♪ La ♪

05:06.367 --> 05:07.803
You're a Taylor swift fan?

05:08.168 --> 05:09.089
They're for Alexis.

05:09.189 --> 05:09.789
Oh.

05:09.856 --> 05:12.303
Cost me an arm and a leg,
but Alexis will be thrilled.

05:12.655 --> 05:15.029
Apparently she and Ash
have a song.

05:15.129 --> 05:16.391
Yeah? Well, we have
a song as well.

05:16.772 --> 05:17.973
- We do?
- Mm-Hmm.

05:18.058 --> 05:19.725
"You Talk Too Much"
by Clarence Carter.

05:19.759 --> 05:21.560
Hey. Funeral director's
story checked out.

05:22.687 --> 05:24.889
- Somebody did break in.
- Did you get any foreign prints

05:24.923 --> 05:25.652
on the casket or the window?

05:25.852 --> 05:26.672
Sorry. Struck out.

05:26.720 --> 05:28.655
But we may have
another at bat.

05:28.689 --> 05:30.857
Dr. Monroe's financials,
and I found something unusual.

05:30.891 --> 05:33.626
Almost every morning,
she bought coffee--

05:33.661 --> 05:36.362
a doctor who buys coffee?
Wow. That is unusual.

05:36.397 --> 05:39.832
It is if the coffee shop is
20 blocks from her apartment.

05:41.260 --> 05:42.294
Maybe it's on her way
to work

05:42.394 --> 05:44.389
Nope.
Complete opposite direction.

05:44.396 --> 05:45.897
Boyfriend
in the neighborhood?

05:45.931 --> 05:47.519
On my way to find out.

05:49.454 --> 05:51.255
Great. Now he's mad at me.

05:51.289 --> 05:53.290
Beckett.

05:53.325 --> 05:56.060
I found these on
the victim's clothes and hair--

05:56.094 --> 05:58.029
Gray nylon.

05:58.063 --> 06:00.275
Carpet fibers?

06:00.375 --> 06:02.195
Sent 'em over to the lab

06:02.240 --> 06:03.132
to see if they could
determine the manufacturer.

06:03.232 --> 06:04.421
How about cause of death?

06:04.621 --> 06:07.556
Well, that's where things
get a little interesting.

06:08.954 --> 06:12.590
The bruise on her head
was made with a blunt object.

06:12.624 --> 06:14.558
Mm-Hmm.
May have knocked her out,

06:14.593 --> 06:17.227
but as I suspected,
it's not what killed her.

06:17.262 --> 06:19.930
I found a needle mark
on the side of her neck.

06:19.998 --> 06:21.652
She was injected
with a syringe.

06:22.196 --> 06:23.663
She was poisoned?

06:23.697 --> 06:25.331
Not exactly.

06:25.366 --> 06:29.068
The killer inserted the needle
of an empty syringe

06:29.103 --> 06:31.604
into Dr. Monroe's
carotid artery,

06:31.639 --> 06:33.106
then pushed the plunger,

06:33.140 --> 06:36.609
forcing air directly into
the brain, causing a fatal--

06:36.644 --> 06:38.978
- air embolism.
- Gold star for Castle.

06:39.013 --> 06:41.181
And judging by the skill
of the injection,

06:41.215 --> 06:43.816
I'd say it was done
by a medical professional.

06:43.851 --> 06:45.692
Like one her colleagues
at County Hospital.

06:45.958 --> 06:48.226
Looks like someone gave her
20 cc's of death.

06:48.261 --> 06:50.729
<font color=#7fff00>♪ Castle 3x05 ♪</font>
