07:00.330 --> 07:02.096
You know,
with the state of health care

07:02.202 --> 07:05.160
and how stressful this can be
for families and for patients,

07:05.246 --> 07:07.214
I'm surprised that
more medical professionals

07:07.248 --> 07:08.281
aren't killed every day.

07:08.381 --> 07:10.006
Yeah, not to mention
the betrayal,

07:10.192 --> 07:12.527
the lust, the bed hopping.

07:12.562 --> 07:14.529
I've watched enough
medical dramas to know

07:14.564 --> 07:17.065
that doctors are notorious
for sleeping with each other.

07:17.099 --> 07:19.668
I bet, as we speak,
in this hospital,

07:19.702 --> 07:22.170
two doctors are
in a break room <i>doing it,</i>

07:22.204 --> 07:24.339
and by "it," I mean--

07:24.373 --> 07:27.342
I know what "it" means, Castle,
and that is just a fantasy.

07:27.376 --> 07:29.177
Four out of five doctors

07:29.211 --> 07:31.061
prefer sleeping with someone
outside of their profession.

07:31.161 --> 07:32.281
Four out of five?

07:32.314 --> 07:32.839
Mm-Hmm.

07:32.939 --> 07:34.059
How many of them
like detectives?

07:34.717 --> 07:36.217
One that I know of.

07:36.252 --> 07:38.219
Whoa. You mean
motorcycle boy is a doctor?

07:38.254 --> 07:41.056
"Man," Castle.
Motorcycle man.

07:41.090 --> 07:42.791
Fine, but he's a doctor?

07:42.825 --> 07:44.526
Yeah, he is.

07:44.560 --> 07:46.094
Huh.

07:46.128 --> 07:48.129
What kind of doctor?
Urologist?

07:48.164 --> 07:49.898
Proctologist?

07:49.932 --> 07:51.900
Don't tell me
he's a gynecologist.

07:51.934 --> 07:52.743
He's a cardiac surgeon.

07:52.843 --> 07:56.246
Oh. A cardiac surgeon.
Wow. That's--

07:56.280 --> 07:57.947
impressive. Yes, it is,

07:57.982 --> 08:01.084
in fact, he did an emergency
bypass on someone this morning,

08:01.118 --> 08:02.585
saved the patient's life.

08:02.620 --> 08:05.455
What'd you do this morning,
Castle?

08:05.489 --> 08:08.324
Made waffles.

08:09.416 --> 08:11.750
A patient could be terminal
and would suddenly just smile

08:11.818 --> 08:14.386
every time Dr. Monroe
walked into a room.

08:14.421 --> 08:16.822
It's a huge, huge loss
for us.

08:16.856 --> 08:18.824
Did she have any family?

08:18.858 --> 08:21.060
Uh, a brother, I think,
in San Diego.

08:21.094 --> 08:22.394
Boyfriend?

08:22.429 --> 08:24.063
Not that she ever mentioned.

08:24.097 --> 08:25.977
She used to always say that
the hospital was her family.

08:26.352 --> 08:28.386
Was there any friction
with any of her colleagues?

08:28.421 --> 08:30.388
Well, yesterday,

08:30.423 --> 08:32.323
just before the end
of her shift,

08:32.357 --> 08:34.692
Dr. Monroe had a private meeting
with one of our nurses.

08:34.727 --> 08:37.062
Is that unusual?

08:37.096 --> 08:39.164
No, but, um, the nurse
came out of the meeting

08:39.198 --> 08:40.832
looking shaken.

08:40.866 --> 08:42.833
I asked Dr. Monroe
about the meeting,

08:42.868 --> 08:45.336
and she said that it was
a personal situation

08:45.371 --> 08:48.073
that she was looking into
and trying to solve.

08:48.107 --> 08:49.841
I'll need to speak
with that nurse.

08:49.875 --> 08:51.409
Nurse McClintock? Of course.

08:51.444 --> 08:53.011
Personal situation
with a nurse--

08:53.045 --> 08:54.579
you thinking
what I'm thinking?

08:54.613 --> 08:56.081
Probably not.

08:56.115 --> 08:57.649
Hospital love triangle.

08:57.683 --> 08:59.651
Check it out--
our dead Dr. Monroe,

08:59.685 --> 09:02.687
she's hot and heavy
with her manly mcdreamy,

09:02.721 --> 09:05.090
until she catches him
in the on-call room

09:05.124 --> 09:07.092
with his scrubs
around his ankles,

09:07.126 --> 09:09.928
shagging
naughty nurse McClintock.

09:09.962 --> 09:11.930
Then the inevitable catfight
ensues

09:11.964 --> 09:14.065
between said nurse
and Dr. Monroe--

09:14.100 --> 09:16.267
a catfight to the death.

09:16.302 --> 09:19.270
Ooh, that's a good title
for something.

09:19.338 --> 09:20.939
"Catfight to the death."

09:20.973 --> 09:23.208
How much TV
do you actually watch?

09:23.242 --> 09:24.321
Enough to know

09:24.377 --> 09:26.498
that this nurse McClintock
will probably be super hot.

09:26.598 --> 09:27.798
Detective.

09:28.047 --> 09:29.576
You wanted to see me.

09:29.676 --> 09:30.515
And you are?

09:30.716 --> 09:33.118
Nurse McClintock.

09:33.152 --> 09:35.120
Care to revise your theory?

09:35.154 --> 09:38.523
Not what I was expecting,
but no, I'll stand by it.

09:38.557 --> 09:40.058
Hey, Greg.

09:40.092 --> 09:42.293
Hey, Dr. Akerman.

09:43.525 --> 09:44.707
So what can I do
for you?

09:44.807 --> 09:46.909
Well, we're here
about Dr. Monroe's murder.

09:47.009 --> 09:48.399
Yeah, it's pretty awful.

09:48.499 --> 09:50.467
We understand that you had
a meeting with her

09:50.501 --> 09:51.975
right before her shift ended
last night.

09:52.049 --> 09:54.083
Yeah. I saw her.

09:54.118 --> 09:56.786
I love the way your hair
frames your face.

09:56.820 --> 09:59.589
Do you always
wear it like that?

09:59.623 --> 10:02.925
Uh, for work, yeah,
but, uh, so about Dr. Monroe?

10:02.960 --> 10:04.393
Hey, Greg.

10:04.428 --> 10:06.162
Hey, Dr. Phelps.

10:06.196 --> 10:09.365
You seem, uh, pretty popular
around here.

10:09.399 --> 10:11.100
Though from what we've heard,

10:11.135 --> 10:13.703
maybe not so much
with Dr. Monroe.

10:13.737 --> 10:16.472
What did you meet with her about
last night?

10:16.507 --> 10:17.940
Nothing, really. It's just,

10:17.975 --> 10:22.071
she thought I was too flirty
with her female residents.

10:22.231 --> 10:23.199
Imagine that.

10:23.299 --> 10:24.419
What's wrong
with being friendly?

10:25.047 --> 10:26.333
So what happened afterwards?

10:26.349 --> 10:28.150
I walked her
to the ambulance dock

10:28.184 --> 10:30.519
and promised to keep
my distance from her residents.

10:30.553 --> 10:32.454
She thanked me,
and then headed off

10:32.488 --> 10:34.389
with some guy
I'd never seen before.

10:34.423 --> 10:36.791
Hmm. So you walked
Dr. Monroe out

10:36.826 --> 10:41.893
and then conveniently saw her
with some mystery man.

10:42.589 --> 10:43.454
That's what happened.

10:43.554 --> 10:44.570
Oh.

10:44.670 --> 10:47.371
Where were you last night
between 7:00 and 9:00?

10:47.406 --> 10:49.473
Are you asking
for my alibi?

10:49.508 --> 10:51.048
- Seriously?
- Seriously.

10:51.052 --> 10:52.242
- Seriously?
- Seriously.

10:52.748 --> 10:54.374
- Seriously?
- Seriously.

10:54.539 --> 10:57.174
Okay. Uh, I was...

10:58.208 --> 10:59.903
Getting coffee with Imani.

11:00.003 --> 11:01.503
I mean, Dr. Phelps.

11:01.538 --> 11:03.005
Uh--
no, wait.

11:03.039 --> 11:04.940
At that time,
I was with Rhonda--

11:04.974 --> 11:07.476
Dr. Chimes.

11:07.510 --> 11:09.212
You can ask her.
She'll verify where I was.

11:09.450 --> 11:11.351
Dr. Rhonda Chimes,
who's smokin' hot, by the way,

11:11.385 --> 11:12.852
confirms his story.

11:12.887 --> 11:15.221
She went on and on about
how Greg's such a great listener

11:15.256 --> 11:18.730
and brings her all these cute
"thinking of you" gifts.

11:18.894 --> 11:21.578
Well, I knew my "homicidal hospital
love triangle" theory had weight.

11:21.678 --> 11:23.278
That makes Greg mcdreamy.

11:23.384 --> 11:25.652
See, that's what I thought,
but Dr. Chimes says

11:25.686 --> 11:27.620
the relationship
was strictly platonic.

11:27.655 --> 11:29.555
So I spoke to more members
of the staff,

11:29.590 --> 11:31.491
and that's when I found
the others.

11:31.525 --> 11:33.059
"The others"?

11:33.093 --> 11:35.295
The other women
in what I call...

11:36.038 --> 11:37.472
The galaxy of Greg.

11:37.498 --> 11:40.678
Each one of these women
orbits Greg

11:40.859 --> 11:43.234
and considers him to be
their special friend.

11:43.315 --> 11:44.809
Well, that totally
makes him mcsteamy.

11:44.850 --> 11:46.751
Nope. Spoke with all
the planets in the galaxy,

11:46.786 --> 11:48.653
and none of them
are sleeping with him.

11:48.687 --> 11:50.555
And C.S.U. did a sweep
of the facility.

11:50.589 --> 11:52.423
None of their carpeting
matches the fibers

11:52.458 --> 11:53.516
they found from the body.

11:53.616 --> 11:55.796
No, makes no sense.
Why spend all that time

11:55.896 --> 11:57.221
listening to women
and buying them things

11:57.321 --> 11:58.630
if you're not gonna try
and sleep with them?

11:59.556 --> 12:00.589
Beckett's here.

12:00.789 --> 12:01.827
Maybe Greg is gay.

12:01.892 --> 12:04.338
With the way he was hitting
on me? No. He's so not gay.

12:04.795 --> 12:06.996
Well, he's working an angle
or he's hiding something.

12:07.031 --> 12:08.765
He's not the only one.

12:08.799 --> 12:10.266
Our victim's student loans.

12:10.301 --> 12:11.801
Since graduating med school,

12:11.835 --> 12:15.171
Dr. Monroe has been regularly
making minimum-amount payments

12:15.205 --> 12:17.610
on her $440,000 student loan.

12:17.710 --> 12:19.368
That's how much it costs
to become a doctor?

12:19.545 --> 12:20.456
Glad I became a cop.

12:20.556 --> 12:22.894
And without any increase
in pay at the hospital,

12:23.459 --> 12:26.141
6 months ago, she started
paying $10,000 a week.

12:26.317 --> 12:28.017
40 grand a month?

12:28.052 --> 12:30.053
Any idea where the money
was coming from?

12:30.087 --> 12:32.122
Not from a bank account.
From money orders.

12:32.156 --> 12:34.224
So someone was making
the payments on her behalf.
Mm-Hmm.

12:34.258 --> 12:36.025
Just got a fax
from hospital security.

12:36.060 --> 12:38.461
They got this off
the ambulance dock camera.

12:38.496 --> 12:40.930
Your boy Greg was telling
the truth. Dr. Monroe did

12:40.965 --> 12:42.429
head out with another guy.
Security showed

12:42.529 --> 12:44.034
this photo around,
but no one recognized him.

12:44.134 --> 12:45.513
Well, whoever this man is,
he might have been

12:45.613 --> 12:47.602
the last one to see
Dr. Monroe alive.

12:47.702 --> 12:48.942
Especially if he killed her.

